wiki.summary: On “Blood On My Jeans,“ Juice WRLD sings/raps about his deep love for his girlfriend, Ally Lotti, and also touches on his usual topics of drugs and weaponry. He notes that when he kills his enemies at close range, their blood splatters onto his jeans. Juice first teased this song during an Instagram Live session on August 27, 2019. On April 4, 2020, Lil Bibby, Juice’s manager, replied to a fan on Instagram, confirming that the track would be on Juice’s first posthumous album. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: On “Blood On My Jeans,“ Juice WRLD sings/raps about his deep love for his girlfriend, Ally Lotti, and also touches on his usual topics of drugs and weaponry. He notes that when he kills his enemies at close range, their blood splatters onto his jeans. Juice first teased this song during an Instagram Live session on August 27, 2019. On April 4, 2020, Lil Bibby, Juice’s manager, replied to a fan on Instagram, confirming that the track would be on Juice’s first posthumous album. On June 27, 2020, Gunna previewed the track during an Instagram Live session, hinting at his appearance on the song. Gezin, the song’s producer, previewed more of the track later that day. However, the final version removes Gunna from the track for unknown reasons. Read more on Last.fm.
